Grading Criteria for "Experiment Aim" Section:

1. Clarity: The aim of the experiment is clearly stated and easy to understand. (1 point)
2. Relevance: The aim of the experiment is relevant to the tasks and scenarios presented in the exercises. (1 point)
3. Completeness: The aim of the experiment includes all the necessary steps and objectives required to complete the exercises. (1 point)
4. Accuracy: The aim of the experiment is technically accurate and free from misconceptions. (1 point)
5. Ambition: The aim of the experiment goes beyond the minimum requirements and demonstrates a clear effort to understand the concepts presented in the exercises. (1 point)

Note: Each requirement fulfillment can be only graded with 0 or 1 point. Non-integer points like 0.5 etc. are forbidden.